<TITLE> Foreign investment depends on budget clarity: Muhith </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 08 (bdnews24.com)The future investments of the European Union in Bangladesh will depend mainly on the upcoming budget's transparency, the finance minister said on Monday. Bangladesh has so far been spared the lashings of the ongoing global economic crunch, AMA Muhith told the visiting European Union Troika delegation. The GDP has not seen any serious regression to date, he said. A seven-member delegation of the Troika, led by Czech Republic's deputy minister Helena Bambasova, met with Muhith on Monday in his office and discussed a number of issues of bilateral interests. After the meeting, the finance minister said they discussed Bangladesh's poverty alleviation, energy issues and the need for further investment. "The EU is a major donor, development and trade associate in our case," said the minister. "Investment increases will be linked to how transparently we are able to handle our financial responsibilities." The formal meeting between Bangladesh and the EU took place after two years, Muhith said. Asked if they discussed war crimes trial, the minister said they had not. b
